article.headline: Boise State 77, San Jose State 75
article.story: SAN JOSE, Calif. (AP) -- Matt Bauscher scored a career-high 22 points to help Boise State defeat San Jose State 77-75 on Wednesday night. Coby Karl scored 16 points, including two free throws that gave the Broncos (11-9, 4-5 Western Athletic Conference) the lead for good in the final 2 minutes. Seth Robinson, who scored 12, added two key free throws with 31 seconds left. Tyler Tiedeman sealed the victory with two fouls shots with 9.1 seconds remaining. Tyree Gardner hit a 3-pointer with 3 seconds remaining but San Jose State (5-15, 1-6) never got off another shot. Karl moved into 13th place on the Boise State career scoring list with his performance. The junior guard now has 1,078 points. Alex Elam scored 19 points to lead the Spartans, who lost their ninth straight home game and 10 of 11 overall. Menelik Barbary had 13 points and Demetrius Brown added 12. Boise State has beaten the Spartans eight straight and 13 of 14 overall. The Spartans opened a 52-42 lead when Elam hit a shot with 14:28 remaining to play but the Broncos went on an 18-5 run over the next five minutes and took a 60-57 advantage when Karl hit a 3-pointer. San Jose State regained the lead at 62-60 when Brown hit a pair of free throws with 7:20 left. The Spartans held on to their slim lead until Karl made his foul shots with 1:56 left to make it 71-70. Boise State ran into foul trouble in the first 20 minutes, with Karl limited to 10 minutes with three fouls and starting senior forward Tez Banks limited to seven minutes with a pair of fouls. San Jose State made seven of 10 field goals during one stretch and took a 34-24 with 4:01 left in the first half but the Broncos recovered and drew within 38-34 at the break.
